tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE streaming_data (
  stream_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  genre_id UUID,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  num_streams INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES music_genres(genre_id)
);

CREATE TABLE genre (genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY, genre_name VARCHAR(255))
CREATE TABLE artist (artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY, artist_name VARCHAR(255), genre_id INT)
CREATE TABLE streaming_data (stream_id INT PRIMARY KEY, artist_id INT, streaming_date DATE, streams INT)
CREATE TABLE Genre (genre_id INT PRIMARY KEY, genre_name VARCHAR(255))
CREATE TABLE Artist (artist_id INT PRIMARY KEY, artist_name VARCHAR(255), genre_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (genre_id) REFERENCES Genre(genre_id))
CREATE TABLE Album (album_id INT PRIMARY KEY, album_name VARCHAR(255), artist_id INT, release_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (artist_id) REFERENCES Artist(artist_id))
CREATE TABLE Song (song_id INT PRIMARY KEY, song_name VARCHAR(255), album_id INT, play_count INT, release_year INT, FOREIGN KEY (album_id) REFERENCES Album(album_id))

CREATE TABLE Genre (id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
          genre_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE Album (id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
          album_title VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
          release_date DATE,
          artist_id UUID REFERENCES Artist(id));

CREATE TABLE Song (id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
          song_title VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
          duration INT,
          album_id UUID REFERENCES Album(id));

CREATE TABLE StreamData (id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
          stream_date DATE,
          song_id UUID REFERENCES Song(id),
          number_of_streams INT);
